        "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
        "body": "Yes, that is correct That should be the defaults on arch, if you refresh, you need to do an upgrade, otherwise you end up with broken so names because pacman does not resolve upgrades to sonames and force other packages to upgrade.\r\n\r\nIf you want to do only a refresh and install, and not upgrade you can end up with an unbootable system, but you can do this by setting `sysupgrade=False` on the commandline with the `refresh=true`",
