    {
        "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
        "body": "We could make `sysupgrade=False` the default, but then we'd have a lot _more_ people complaining about broken systems from unsupported partial upgrades (though, likely with far more tact than you displayed).\r\n\r\nPlease read this [article](https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/System_maintenance#Partial_upgrades_are_unsupported) from the ArchWiki so that you can better understand the reason for making `sysupgrade=True` the default.\r\n\r\nHave a nice day!",
